## Comprehensive Vue 3 + TypeScript Frontend Analysis

I've completed a thorough exploration of your Developer Blog Platform frontend. Here's a detailed breakdown of the existing patterns to guide your engagement features:

---

### 1. API CLIENT SETUP (src/api/)

**HTTP Client: `/src/api/http.ts`**
- **Base URL**: `/api` (Vite proxy handles routing to `http://localhost:8080`)
- **Axios Instance**: Configured with JSON content-type headers
- **Request Interceptor**: Automatically injects `Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;` from auth store
- **Response Interceptor** (Smart Token Refresh):
  - On 401: Initiates one refresh attempt using stored `refreshToken`
  - **Queue Pattern**: Concurrent requests during refresh are queued and retried with new token
  - **Circular Dependency Fix**: Lazy imports auth store to avoid circular dependencies
  - Failed refresh triggers auto-logout and clears stored tokens
  - Auth endpoints exempt from retry logic to prevent infinite loops

**Type Definitions: `/src/api/types.ts`**
- `PostResponse` / `PostSummaryResponse` - full/summary posts with author, category, view count, tags
- `UserResponse` - user profile with username, email, displayName, bio, avatarUrl, roles, active status
- `AuthResponse` - login/register returns access/refresh tokens + user
- `Page&lt;T&gt;` - pagination: `{ content: T[], totalElements, totalPages, number, size, first, last }`
- `ApiError` - standardized error with timestamp, status, message, fieldErrors

**API Endpoint Modules**:
- **`/src/api/auth.ts`**: `register()`, `login()`, `refresh()`, `logout()`
- **`/src/api/posts.ts`**:
  - Public: `listPublished({ category?, search?, sort: 'latest'|'popular', page?, size? })`, `getBySlug(slug)`
  - Authenticated: `listMine({ status?, page?, size? })`, `getMine(id)`, `create()`, `update()`, `changeStatus()`, `remove()`
- **`/src/api/users.ts`**:
  - Profile: `getMe()`, `updateMe({ displayName?, bio?, avatarUrl?, email? })`, `changePassword()`
  - Admin: `listUsers({ page?, size?, search? })`, `getUser(id)`, `updateRoles(id, { roles })`, `updateStatus(id, { active })`
- **`/src/api/categories.ts`**: `list()`, `getBySlug(slug)`, `create()`, `update()`, `remove()`

---

### 2. STATE MANAGEMENT (src/stores/)

**Auth Store: `/src/stores/auth.ts`** (Pinia)
```typescript
// State
accessToken: string | null          // Synced to localStorage
refreshToken: string | null         // Synced to localStorage
currentUser: UserResponse | null
loading: boolean

// Computed getters
isAuthenticated: boolean            // !!accessToken
isAdmin: boolean                    // currentUser?.roles.includes('ADMIN')
isUser: boolean                     // currentUser?.roles.includes('USER')

// Actions
register(data: RegisterRequest): Promise&lt;void&gt;
login(data: LoginRequest): Promise&lt;void&gt;
logout(): Promise&lt;void&gt;              // Best-effort async API call, clears state immediately
refresh(): Promise&lt;string&gt;           // Returns new access token
loadMe(): Promise&lt;void&gt;              // Fetches currentUser if authenticated
```

**Token Persistence**:
- Keys: `'devblog_access_token'`, `'devblog_refresh_token'`
- On init: Rehydrates from localStorage and calls `loadMe()` if token exists
- This allows page refresh to restore authenticated state

---

### 3. VIEWS (src/views/)

**PostDetailView.vue** (`/posts/:slug`)
- Fetches post via `postsApi.getBySlug(slug)`
- Renders markdown content via `MarkdownPreview` component
- **Loading/Error/NotFound States**: Spinner, 404 message, error alert
- **Edit Button Logic**: Shows for post author OR admins (checks `auth.currentUser?.id === post.author.id`)
- **Layout**: Hero title with category chip, author avatar/name, date, divider, markdown body, back link
- **Date Formatting**: Uses published or created date with locale formatter

**PostsListView.vue** (public, `/`)
- Grid of `PostCard` components (3 columns on desktop)
- **Filtering**:
  - Search (debounced 350ms)
  - Category filter (dropdown of categories fetched on mount)
  - Sort: "latest" or "most popular"
- **Pagination**: Page size 12, displays total elements &amp; page count
- **Loading State**: Skeleton cards grid
- **Tag Click**: Emitted from PostCard, triggers search query update
- Fetches posts via `postsApi.listPublished()` with filter params

**MyPostsView.vue** (`/me/posts`, protected)
- Table of user's posts with status filter tabs (ALL/DRAFT/PUBLISHED)
- **Per-post Actions**: Edit, Publish/Unpublish toggle, Delete with confirmation
- **Per-row State**: `actioning[postId]` tracks loading during mutations
- In-place updates after status/delete operations

**ProfileView.vue** (`/profile`, protected)
- **Read-only Info**: Username, avatar initial, roles badges (ADMIN/USER color-coded), join date
- **Profile Form**: Email, displayName, bio, avatarUrl with validation
- **Password Form**: Current, new, confirm with match validation
- **Form Validation**: Uses `useFormValidation` composable with server error mapping
- **Success/Error Messages**: Alert components displayed after actions

**Admin Views**:
- **UsersView.vue** (`/admin/users`): Paginated table with search, role toggles (ADMIN/USER buttons), activate/deactivate
- **CategoriesView.vue** (`/admin/categories`): Create/edit panel, delete confirmation

---

### 4. COMPONENTS (src/components/)

**Reusable Components**:

| Component | Purpose | Key Props/Events |
|-----------|---------|------------------|
| `PostCard.vue` | Grid card for post summary | `post: PostSummaryResponse`, `showStatus?`, emits `@tagClick` |
| `MarkdownPreview.vue` | Renders markdown to HTML safely | `content: string` (uses markdown-it + DOMPurify) |
| `AppButton.vue` | Styled button with loading state | `variant: 'primary'/'secondary'/'danger'/'ghost'`, `loading?`, `fullWidth?`, `disabled?` |
| `AlertMessage.vue` | Colored alert boxes | `type: 'error'/'success'/'info'`, `message: string` |
| `FormField.vue` | Label + error/hint wrapper | `id`, `label`, `error?`, `hint?` |
| `AppInput.vue` | Styled input field | `v-model`, `type`, `placeholder`, `hasError?`, `disabled?` |
| `StatusBadge.vue` | Post status indicator | `status: PostStatus` (shows "published" or "draft") |
