**Styling Patterns**:
- All components use **inline styles** with CSS variables for colors (no Tailwind classes in components)
- Color palette from `/src/style.css`:
  - `#0D1117` (ink background)
  - `#161B22` (surface)
  - `#30363D` (borders)
  - `#E6A817` (amber accent)
  - `#E6EDF3` (light text)
  - `#F85149` (danger), `#3FB950` (success)
- Fonts: `JetBrains Mono` (display/mono), `Inter` (body)

---

### 5. ROUTER (src/router/index.ts)

**Route Guards**:
```typescript
Meta flags: { public?, requiresAuth?, requiresAdmin?, redirectIfAuth? }

// Global beforeEach guard logic:
- redirectIfAuth: Redirects authenticated users from /login, /register to /
- requiresAuth: Redirects unauthenticated to /login with redirect query param
- requiresAdmin: Calls loadMe() if token exists but user not loaded, then checks isAdmin
```

**Public Routes**: `/`, `/login`, `/register`, `/posts/:slug`

**Protected Routes**: `/profile`, `/posts/new`, `/posts/:id/edit`, `/me/posts`

**Admin Routes**: `/admin/users`, `/admin/categories`

---

### 6. COMPOSABLES (src/composables/)

**`useFormValidation.ts`**:
```typescript
function useFormValidation&lt;T extends Record&lt;string, string&gt;&gt;(fields: T) {
  return {
    errors: Ref&lt;Partial&lt;Record&lt;keyof T, string&gt;&gt;&gt;,
    validate(rules: { [K in keyof T]?: ValidationRule&lt;string&gt;[] }): boolean,
    setFieldError(field, message | null): void,
    clearErrors(): void,
    setServerErrors(fieldErrors: Record&lt;string, string&gt;): void
  }
}

// Built-in rules: required, minLength, maxLength, email, matches, noSpaces
```

Used in ProfileView and auth forms to validate and display field-level errors. Can map backend `fieldErrors` object directly.

