### 5. REPOSITORIES

**Location:** `C:\projects\develop_blog\backend\devblog\devblog\src\main\java\met\ivan\devblog\repository\`

#### **PostRepository** extends `JpaRepository&lt;Post, Long&gt;, JpaSpecificationExecutor&lt;Post&gt;`
```java
// Custom queries with JOIN FETCH (avoid N+1)
@Query("SELECT p FROM Post p JOIN FETCH p.author LEFT JOIN FETCH p.category WHERE p.slug = :slug")
Optional&lt;Post&gt; findBySlug(String slug);

@Query("SELECT p FROM Post p JOIN FETCH p.author LEFT JOIN FETCH p.category WHERE p.slug = :slug AND p.status = :status")
Optional&lt;Post&gt; findBySlugAndStatus(String slug, PostStatus status);

@Query("SELECT p FROM Post p JOIN FETCH p.author LEFT JOIN FETCH p.category WHERE p.id = :id")
Optional&lt;Post&gt; findByIdWithAuthorAndCategory(Long id);

// View count atomic increment
@Modifying
@Query("UPDATE Post p SET p.viewCount = p.viewCount + 1 WHERE p.id = :id")
void incrementViewCount(Long id);

// Simple existence checks
boolean existsBySlug(String slug);
boolean existsByCategory(Category category);
long countByAuthorUsername(String username);
```

**Filtering:** Uses `Specification&lt;Post&gt;` pattern (buildPublishedSpec, buildOwnSpec in service)

#### **UserRepository** extends `JpaRepository&lt;User, Long&gt;, JpaSpecificationExecutor&lt;User&gt;`
```java
// All fetch roles eagerly to avoid N+1
@Query("SELECT u FROM User u JOIN FETCH u.roles WHERE u.username = :username")
Optional&lt;User&gt; findByUsernameWithRoles(String username);

@Query("SELECT u FROM User u JOIN FETCH u.roles WHERE u.email = :email")
Optional&lt;User&gt; findByEmailWithRoles(String email);

@Query("SELECT u FROM User u JOIN FETCH u.roles WHERE u.username = :usernameOrEmail OR u.email = :usernameOrEmail")
Optional&lt;User&gt; findByUsernameOrEmailWithRoles(String usernameOrEmail);

// For login scenarios that accept username OR email
Optional&lt;User&gt; findByUsername(String username);
Optional&lt;User&gt; findByEmail(String email);

// Existence checks
boolean existsByUsername(String username);
boolean existsByEmail(String email);
boolean existsByEmailAndIdNot(String email, Long id);  // For unique validation on update
```

