### 7. SECURITY

**Location:** `C:\projects\develop_blog\backend\devblog\devblog\src\main\java\met\ivan\devblog\security\` and `config/SecurityConfig.java`

#### **JWT Authentication Flow**

**JwtService** — Token generation &amp; validation
```java
// Access token: contains username + roles claim
String generateAccessToken(UserDetails userDetails)
    // Claims: subject=username, roles=[ROLE_ADMIN, ROLE_USER], type=access
    // Signed with 256-bit HMAC-SHA key
    // Expires: configurable (default 15 min)

// Refresh token: opaque, stored in DB
String generateRefreshToken(UserDetails userDetails)
    // Claims: id=UUID, subject=username, type=refresh
    // Expires: configurable (default 7 days)

// Validation
boolean isTokenValid(String token, UserDetails userDetails)
    // Verifies signature, expiration, username match
```

**JwtAuthenticationFilter** — Per-request JWT extraction
```java
// Runs before UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter
// Extracts "Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;" header
// On valid JWT:
//   - Extracts username and roles from claims
//   - Loads UserDetails via CustomUserDetailsService
//   - Creates UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken with ROLE_* authorities
//   - Sets in SecurityContextHolder
// On invalid JWT: continues unauthenticated (doesn't block)
```

**CustomUserDetailsService** — UserDetails loader
```java
// Implements UserDetailsService
// loadUserByUsername() accepts username OR email
// Fetches User with roles eagerly via JPA query
// Maps roles: RoleName.ADMIN → authority "ROLE_ADMIN"
// Returns Spring Security User with authorities
```

#### **SecurityConfig** — HTTP Authorization Rules
```java
@EnableWebSecurity
@EnableMethodSecurity  // Enables @PreAuthorize annotations

// Key configurations:
csrf().disable() — No CSRF protection (API, JWT-based)
sessionManagement(STATELESS) — No server-side sessions
cors(corsConfigurationSource()) — Configurable origins

// Path-based authorization:
/api/auth/** → permitAll
/api/admin/** → hasRole(ADMIN)
/api/users/** → authenticated

// Post endpoints:
GET /api/posts (public) → permitAll
GET /api/posts/{slug} (public) → permitAll
GET /api/posts/mine, POST, PUT, DELETE → authenticated

// Exception handling:
401 Unauthorized → "Authentication required"
403 Forbidden → "Access denied"

// CORS configuration:
allowedOrigins: ${CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS} (default: http://localhost:5173)
allowedMethods: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS, PATCH
allowedHeaders: Authorization, Content-Type, Accept
exposedHeaders: Authorization
credentials: true, maxAge: 3600
```

#### **Role-Based Access**
```java
// In service layer:
if (author.getRoles().stream().anyMatch(r -&gt; r.getName() == RoleName.ADMIN)) {
    throw new ForbiddenOperationException("Admins cannot author posts");
}

// Owner/Admin check pattern:
private void assertOwnerOrAdmin(Post post, UserDetails principal) {
    boolean isAdmin = principal.getAuthorities().stream()
        .map(GrantedAuthority::getAuthority)
        .anyMatch(a -&gt; a.equals("ROLE_ADMIN"));
    boolean isOwner = post.getAuthor().getUsername().equals(principal.getUsername());
    if (!isOwner &amp;&amp; !isAdmin) {
        throw new ForbiddenOperationException("...");
    }
}
```

